主要翻译
 
!! pile n (heap)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 堆 duī TC Traditional Chinese 堆  
 -- Teenagers often have a pile of dirty clothes on their bedroom floors.
 -- 青少年的卧室地板上总是扔着一堆脏衣服。
 
a pile of [sth] n informal, figurative, often plural (large amount)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 大量，很多 dà liàng ，hěn duō TC Traditional Chinese 大量  
 -- Irene couldn't go out as she had a pile of work to do.
 -- 艾琳有很多工作要做，不能外出。
 
a pile n figurative, slang (money: large amount)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 大笔财富  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 巨款 jù kuǎn 
 -- Michelle made a pile on the stock market.
 -- 米歇尔在股市上挣了一大笔钱。
 
pile n (carpet thickness)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 绒毛 róng máo TC Traditional Chinese 絨毛  (地毯等)
 -- This carpet has a lovely thick pile.
 -- 这张地毯有一层可爱的厚绒毛。
 
piles npl informal (hemorrhoids)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 痔疮 zhì chuāng  
 -- Josh is going to see the doctor about his piles.
 -- 乔希要去找医生看痔疮。
 
pile [sth] # vtr (make into a pile, stack)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 堆砌 duī qì  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 堆起 duī qì ，duī qǐ 
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 堆叠 
 -- Steve piled the food on the plate.
 -- 史蒂夫在盘中堆满了食物。

其他翻译
 
pile n (construction)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 高大宏伟的建筑  

主要翻译
 
piled, -piled, pile, -pile adj (textile: wooly, hairy)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 有细毛的，绒面的  (织物)
 -- 备注 : Often used in combination: e.g., deep-piled

动词短语  pile  |  piled
 
pile in vi phrasal informal (crowd inside: a vehicle)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 坠毁 zhuì huǐ  
 -- The taxi pulled up outside the house and we all piled in.
 
pile on vi phrasal figurative, informal (join in: with criticism, etc.)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 参与批评  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 一个劲地批评 
 
pile up vi phrasal informal (accumulate)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 积累 jī lěi TC Traditional Chinese 積累 / 累積  (非正式用语)
 -- While his wife was gone, Sam let the dishes pile up in the sink.
 -- 萨姆妻子不在时，他将碗碟都堆放在水槽里。
 
pile [sth] up, pile up [sth] vtr phrasal sep (place on top of one another)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 堆积 duī jī TC Traditional Chinese 堆積  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 堆叠 
 -- The toddler piled up the blocks.
 -- 那个小孩将积木堆叠起来。
 
pile [sth] up, pile up [sth] vtr phrasal sep figurative, informal (accumulate)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 积累 jī lěi TC Traditional Chinese 積累 / 累積  (非正式用语)
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 积聚 jī lěi ，jī jù TC Traditional Chinese 積聚 
 -- My boss is piling up the projects and I don't know when I'll have time to finish them all.
 -- 我老板将项目都堆积起来，我不知道什么时候才能全部做完。

复合形式：  pile  |  piled
 
