           --> SC Simplified Chinese 挤进 jǐ jìn  
 -- The seven of us piled into her little car and off we went.
 
pile [sth] on, pile on [sth] vtr + prep (heap)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 堆积...  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 往...上堆 
 -- Robert piled some more coal on the fire.
 
pile on the [sth] vtr + prep figurative, informal (guilt, pressure: inflict)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 增加负担  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 加重压力 
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 加重负罪感 
 -- My grandmother really knows how to pile on the guilt; if I don't go to see her for a few days, she makes me feel terrible.
 
pile on the [sth] vtr + prep figurative, informal (work, etc.: impose)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 增加...工作量  
 -- The boss has really been piling on the work lately; I'm struggling to keep up with it.
 
pile [sth] on [sb] vtr + prep figurative, informal (work, etc.: impose on)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 给某人增加某事的工作量  
 -- Our maths teacher is piling the homework on us this term; I'm struggling to keep up.
 
pile-on n figurative, informal (concerted attack, criticism)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 一致的攻击  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 一致的议论 
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 一致的批评 
 
pile on the pounds v expr informal (gain a lot of weight)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 长胖了许多  
 
pileup, pile-up n informal (crash involving many vehicles)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 连环相撞，连环撞车 lián huán xiāng zhuàng，lián huán zhuàng chē  (非正式用语)
 -- Traffic was stopped because of the pileup on the highway.
 
pileup, pile-up n informal (accumulation)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 累积，堆积 lěi jī，duī jī TC Traditional Chinese 累積，堆積  (非正式用语)
 -- Bob felt overwhelmed by the pileup of documents on his desk.
 
shag, shag pile n as adj (carpet: with long pile)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 长绒地毯 cháng róng dì tǎn TC Traditional Chinese 長絨地毯  
 -- There was a shag carpet in the middle of the floor.
 
